Dialogue: 0,0:00:01.19,0:00:07.35,Default,,0,0,0,,The most crucial moment in life is during decision making.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:09.15,0:00:13.80,Default,,0,0,0,,The Pacific War taught us the preciousness of peace.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:14.26,0:00:19.42,Default,,0,0,0,,But also instilled \Nnumerous lessons on how to live.{unsure, lit is "for the sake of living, precepts, numerous left behind"}
Dialogue: 0,0:00:24.39,0:00:31.39,Sign,,0,0,0,,{\fade(100,700)\c&H0007DF&\fs100\b1\bord0\blur1}Animentary\N{\b\c&HE0DBF3&}Decision
Dialogue: 0,0:00:35.41,0:00:43.33,Default,,0,0,20,,Wit is your weapon{honestly no clue what is megurase here, deepl says "rack one's brain"}\NRemember to use your head{智恵をめぐらせ 頭を使え}
Dialogue: 0,0:00:43.33,0:00:50.95,Default,,0,0,20,,Repress your anguish, \NIf you are a man{悩み抜け抜け 男なら}
Dialogue: 0,0:00:50.95,0:00:58.86,Default,,0,0,20,,One decision is enough \NTo make others cry or laugh{泣くも笑うも 決断ひとつ}
Dialogue: 0,0:00:58.86,0:01:06.69,Default,,0,0,20,,If you win, don't hold your head high, \NIf you lose, don't cry{勝っておごるな 敗れて泣くな}
Dialogue: 0,0:01:06.69,0:01:14.57,Default,,0,0,20,,Men, don't you ever let other see your tears{男 涙は見せぬもの}
Comment: 0,0:01:34.91,0:01:34.95,Default,,0,0,0,,{ch}
Dialogue: 0,0:01:55.74,0:01:58.57,Default,,0,0,0,,December of 1941.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:58.57,0:02:01.91,Default,,0,0,0,,In order to capture \NSouthern Asia's resources by force,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:01.91,0:02:06.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Japan had deployed its Combined fleet \Nin the vast waters of Southern Pacific.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:06.06,0:02:11.46,Default,,0,0,0,,According to the Southern strategy, the unit, \Ntasked with protecting the operation's flanks and rear,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:11.46,0:02:13.25,Default,,0,0,0,,is the First Mobile Fleet -{https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/1st_Air_Fleet}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:13.96,0:02:18.76,Default,,0,0,0,,a large unit of 30 ships, \Nwith 6 aircraft carriers as the core.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:19.65,0:02:25.72,Sign,,0,0,270,,{\fade(200,300)\c&HFEFDFF&\b1\fs50\blur1\bord0}Episode 1 \N{\fs80}Surprise attack on Pearl Harbor{真珠湾奇襲}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:29.65,0:02:33.48,Default,,0,0,0,,On the fateful day, December 8th, at dawn,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:34.11,0:02:38.88,Default,,0,0,0,,the 1st Mobile Fleet carried out \Na secret 5800km expedition,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:38.88,0:02:43.28,Default,,0,0,0,,creeping in the waters \N360 km north of the bay of Pearl Harbor.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:30.61,0:03:33.81,Default,,0,0,0,,Chief, the task force is ready for sortie.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:36.04,0:03:36.88,Default,,0,0,0,,I have...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:38.84,0:03:41.59,Default,,0,0,0,,been in charge of getting us all up to here, but now...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:42.05,0:03:43.14,Default,,0,0,0,,The rest is up to you.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:46.51,0:03:50.70,Default,,0,0,0,,The latest Intel arrived. \NEnemy forces anchored at Pearl Harbor are as follows:
Dialogue: 0,0:03:50.70,0:03:55.91,Default,,0,0,0,,Battleship - 9, second-class cruiser{乙巡} - 3, \Nseaplane tender{水上機母艦} - 3, destroyer{駆逐艦} - 17.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:55.91,0:04:00.78,Default,,0,0,0,,Aircraft carriers and heavy cruisers{重巡} are dispatched. \NNo countermeasure is afoot.{unsure what he means, either "the enemy doesn't suspect a thing" or "the fleet is out of military readiness" - lit is "in fleet, abnormal air/mood/atmosphere not registered"}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:03.93,0:04:05.78,Default,,0,0,0,,The aircraft carrier is not there?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:06.81,0:04:09.58,Default,,0,0,0,,But since it's Sunday, \Nit should be back until tomorrow.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:09.58,0:04:11.27,Default,,0,0,0,,Any chance to cross path with it?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:11.27,0:04:12.66,Default,,0,0,0,,If so, we have the upper hand.{unsure if this is what he means, maybe its "we have an advantage if we meet it here"}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:12.66,0:04:14.33,Default,,0,0,0,,But Pearl Harbor gets alerted.{/we won't go to PH then}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:14.33,0:04:16.63,Default,,0,0,0,,Does it matter?{/isn't that fine, too?} \NA sunken carrier is just as good.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:17.79,0:04:18.71,Default,,0,0,0,,It's time.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:18.71,0:04:20.55,Default,,0,0,0,,Got it! Sir, if you excuse me.{/yes, I am going}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:22.16,0:04:23.59,Default,,0,0,0,,Counting on you!{/do it properly/take care}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:30.29,0:04:34.54,Default,,0,0,0,,If the enemy's carrier spots us, \Nwithout the attack party to guard us, we're screwed.{unsure if it's not "it's not propitious for us to get the attack group getting spotted by enemy kubo after it gets off"}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:34.54,0:04:36.56,Default,,0,0,0,,The 2nd wave wings will hold its own!{lit is "The re-attack force remains" - what does that mean? no se... maybe a reserve forces, maybe a spare group of planes, e.g. preparing for the next sortie?; later this word is reused, there I went with "second wave of attack"}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:36.56,0:04:39.15,Default,,0,0,0,,The price of such defense is still a few ships!{/this is bad, too}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:40.32,0:04:41.82,Default,,0,0,0,,What did I tell you before?{unsure what he means, lit is "the thing I want to say..."}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:41.82,0:04:43.20,Default,,0,0,0,,Chop the Gordian Knot!{一刀両断 is taking decisive action; dealing with decisively; cutting the (Gordian) knot​}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:43.20,0:04:46.20,Default,,0,0,0,,Precisely! Go there and do what you do best!{/go wild to your heart's content}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:55.81,0:04:59.67,Default,,0,0,0,,The first ones to take off \Nare carrier-based fighters of the Zero type. {no clue what is kainin}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:59.67,0:05:01.25,Default,,0,0,0,,Also known as Zero Fighters.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:01.25,0:05:05.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Equipped with two 20mm cannons, \Nthey're a maneuverability-focused aircraft.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:05.80,0:05:08.22,Default,,0,0,0,,It particularly excels in dog-fighting.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:08.22,0:05:11.14,Default,,0,0,0,,This is the main fighter of the Japanese Navy.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:11.60,0:05:13.81,Sign,,0,0,0,,{\c&H26217B&\blur1\3c&HCECCCB&\fade(0,150)}Victory by all means{勝必}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:12.47,0:05:13.18,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm off!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:25.24,0:05:28.66,Default,,0,0,0,,Next goes Nakajima B5N.{/Type 97 carrier-based attack aircraft - 九七式艦上攻撃機}{no clue what is this first word, kaigo?}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:28.66,0:05:31.47,Default,,0,0,0,,It is capable of carrying \Nup 800kg of torpedoes,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:31.47,0:05:34.35,Default,,0,0,0,,while making incursions far behind enemy lines. {/its features include boarding/crossing over into the distant enemy camp}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:34.35,0:05:39.46,Default,,0,0,0,,This aircraft's object of prestige \Nis its horizontal bombing accuracy rate of over 50%.{/it boasts its horizontal torpedoing accuracy rate which is always 50% and more}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:57.69,0:05:59.35,Default,,0,0,0,,If only I were younger...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:59.35,0:06:00.35,Default,,0,0,0,,You'd fly, too?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:00.35,0:06:02.15,Default,,0,0,0,,Of course. With the vanguards!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:04.28,0:06:11.89,Default,,0,0,0,,6:05, 1st wave wings take off, \Nwhile at 7:15, the 2nd wave would follow.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:11.89,0:06:16.05,Default,,0,0,0,,A total of 350 aircraft, \Nwith 765 people in them
Dialogue: 0,0:06:16.05,0:06:19.46,Default,,0,0,0,,folding into one huge formation \Nin the midst of Pacific Ocean.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:19.46,0:06:22.63,Default,,0,0,0,,Right now, they are about \Nto change the course of history.{lit: plunge into history}
Dialogue: 0,0:06:31.93,0:06:34.97,Default,,0,0,0,,Among those, the Aichi D3A carrier-based bomber.{again, no clue what is that kaigo}{九九式艦上爆撃機}
Dialogue: 0,0:06:34.97,0:06:38.69,Default,,0,0,0,,During a nose dive, it has an accuracy rate of 80%.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:38.69,0:06:42.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Pilots put infinite trust in this model.{/have absolute confidence in its performance.}
Dialogue: 0,0:07:01.04,0:07:02.73,Default,,0,0,0,,Awfully cloudy up here.{lit: terrible cloud}
Dialogue: 0,0:07:02.73,0:07:05.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Captain, if our inroad agrees \Nwith Honolulu program,{放送} we'll be ok.{unsure what he means and what's that tagutte word, most likely "follow/trace" but still not sure what it means - maybe "we will know everything if we listen to ..." or "in these clouds, we won't lose our way if we fly towards ..."(unlikely)} {Captain, by listening to Honolulu broadcat we'll always be up to speed.}
Dialogue: 0,0:07:05.92,0:07:08.47,Default,,0,0,0,,They're unaware so far. \NCarefree jazz's playing.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:08.47,0:07:10.09,Default,,0,0,0,,And now, a weather forecast.{why is honolulu radio broadcasting in japanese? fuck if I know}
Dialogue: 0,0:07:09.49,0:07:10.41,Default,,0,0,0,,Hold on!{/Wait!}
Dialogue: 0,0:07:10.41,0:07:15.12,Default,,0,0,0,,Over Oahu, the sky is partly cloudy. \NThe wind blows at about 7.5 knots per hour.{guess, soku may mean anything, but I found related meanings of "velocity" and "measurement" so I'd assume it's this; also can't hear a thing past "nanaten" - 7-point}
Dialogue: 0,0:07:25.61,0:07:28.03,Default,,0,0,0,,Hey, our foes are nice enough to share the forecast!{lit: enemies-san waiting so hard, they even told us the weather}
Dialogue: 0,0:07:34.82,0:07:39.54,Default,,0,0,0,,Beware, {I rather hear "shittekure/ittekure" but it makes the following line too perplexing so I have to agree with HA here}you're forgetting \Nthere are still plenty of Japanese living on Hawaii. {about 158,000 during WW2 according to sources, which is 1/3 of the total population (Ziusudra)}
Dialogue: 0,0:07:39.54,0:07:44.33,Default,,0,0,0,,Nothing exploitable on the radio.{/no reason for us to listen to radio} \NOnly distraction from the hell captain is taking us to.{unsure what he means to say with that whole thing: to taicho-san letting him bring us to the bottom of hell}
Dialogue: 0,0:07:45.02,0:07:46.09,Default,,0,0,0,,We're at Oahu.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:46.84,0:07:48.41,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, it's beautiful...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:49.97,0:07:52.84,Default,,0,0,0,,A heaven on earth. \NSuch a pity to carpet bomb it.{/It's a waste to bomb.}
Dialogue: 0,0:07:58.26,0:08:01.02,Default,,0,0,0,,Alright, we're closing in! \NAssault formation!{/start attack}
Dialogue: 0,0:08:35.24,0:08:37.68,Default,,0,0,0,,The squadron commander just reported back.{/received [something] from captain's plane}
Dialogue: 0,0:08:38.14,0:08:39.64,Default,,0,0,0,,It is action time, isn't it?{/tiger tiger tiger/is attack underway/decided}
Dialogue: 0,0:08:56.47,0:09:00.41,Default,,0,0,0,,Admiral{choukan is technically not exactly military title, but "secretary (government); director; chief" however later down this episode, they call every superior this way, regardless of the situation/standing so I'll make it "admiral"}, the captain's plane \Njust transmitted the assault signal.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:01.04,0:09:02.12,Default,,0,0,0,,Admiral...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:02.12,0:09:04.04,Default,,0,0,0,,They've done it. They made it there!{didnt they}
Dialogue: 0,0:09:04.04,0:09:06.04,Default,,0,0,0,,The break was successful!{absolute guess, HA has is "successful attack" and I'm compelled to agree, no clue what is shichu and senko literally has a million meanings}
Dialogue: 0,0:09:12.30,0:09:14.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Alright, stick to the battle plans!{/quickly start fighting all over the area}
Dialogue: 0,0:09:18.43,0:09:22.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Thus, war hell had broken lose \Nacross the Pacific.{``Hibuta'' means ``a lid that covers the crater of a matchlock gun (of old guns).'' to shoot. This has come to be used in the sense of "starting things, starting action, starting competitions and battles."}
Dialogue: 0,0:09:22.60,0:09:24.27,Default,,0,0,0,,The enemy is still unaware?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:25.17,0:09:26.87,Default,,0,0,0,,Two carriers are missing.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:27.77,0:09:32.23,Default,,0,0,0,,Are they? Whatever. They'll get ambushed \Non their way back by the 2nd wave wings.{lit: if we lure them out now (I think he rather means lure in), we'll definitely hit them during the re-attack (yes, this word again)}
Dialogue: 0,0:09:48.92,0:09:50.07,Default,,0,0,0,,Engage!{/shoot}
Dialogue: 0,0:10:36.13,0:10:37.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Damn you!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:21.26,0:11:24.93,Default,,0,0,0,,Would you just look at this mess?{/just look at this appearance} \NOur fleet is blown to smithereens!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:24.93,0:11:28.27,Default,,0,0,0,,I saw it. I saw it all. \NI was still in my nightwear when it started.{trusting HA here}
Dialogue: 0,0:11:38.90,0:11:41.61,Default,,0,0,0,,Admirals, it is portentous \Nfor you to both stay here.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:41.61,0:11:43.95,Default,,0,0,0,,If you died on-duty \Nwho would take the reins?{/who will take command of ...}
Dialogue: 0,0:11:43.95,0:11:46.74,Default,,0,0,0,,Fine, I'll hide away \Nin the office on the opposite side.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:49.90,0:11:52.24,Default,,0,0,0,,Still, look at the havoc the Japs wrecked on!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:52.24,0:11:55.79,Default,,0,0,0,,I will notify the aircraft carriers \Nso that they push the enemy out.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:20.78,0:12:24.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Alright, anti-aircraft is annihilated.{no clue what's first word, but sounds close to "ground attack; air-raid" so it must be fighters} \NNow, it's naval bombers' turn to act!{lit is rather "sailor bomber"}
Dialogue: 0,0:13:20.92,0:13:23.53,Default,,0,0,0,,Alright, 1st wave wings are done dropping thunder.{either he means "all vehicles in the ... had carried out their duty/shot at the enemy and are now returning" or "... is returning in its entirety/without losses"}
Dialogue: 0,0:13:23.53,0:13:26.72,Default,,0,0,0,,30 minutes before 2nd wave shows up.\NTake a good picture of the damage.{senka can be both "war; wartime destruction; horrors of war​/war damage; ravages of war; horrors of war" and "battleship" but I think HA tripped over this time}
Dialogue: 0,0:13:27.04,0:13:27.69,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:37.21,0:14:40.71,Default,,0,0,0,,The alleged Japanese parachute unit landing \Nwas but a hoax.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:41.57,0:14:44.25,Default,,0,0,0,,Great strategy, even though it's from the enemy.{/it was a brilliant strategy, even though we are enemies}
Dialogue: 0,0:14:45.29,0:14:46.32,Default,,0,0,0,,A sweeping blow.{HA has it "It is a surprise attack." but I think it's rather a "sweep motion" fu for blow and uchi for strike}
Dialogue: 0,0:14:50.43,0:14:53.74,Default,,0,0,0,,What's that talk? Our tax dollars \Ngo to patch up these surprises! {I think he means "This strategy is only applicable when you are stronger." as if "when the enemy cannot replenish those losses"}
Dialogue: 0,0:14:53.74,0:14:58.77,Default,,0,0,0,,Now that they've done their worst, there's no doubt \Nour people will repay this treachery.{unsure, lit: we're supposed to use all our provision/taxes in every such case}
Dialogue: 0,0:15:01.05,0:15:01.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Admiral!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:06.53,0:15:10.61,Default,,0,0,0,,Just a spent Japanese bullet? \NIt would have been merciful if it had killed me. {/How come it didn't pierce my chest as well?}{refers to the shooting of admiral Husband E. Kimmel, as he was on the lookout at the submarine base with communication officer Maurice "Germany" Curts (context clarification from Perevodildo)}{replaced with what kimmel originally said, for shits and giggles}
Dialogue: 0,0:15:14.99,0:15:19.66,Default,,0,0,0,,Alright, done checking the aftermaths.{/I've seen the results of battle}\NNo more latecomers left behind.{lit: we have no allies anymore} Time to withdraw.{lit: pull back}
Dialogue: 0,0:15:40.88,0:15:42.77,Default,,0,0,0,,Jettison that pile of scrap!{/Throw the broken fighter into the sea!}
Dialogue: 0,0:15:42.77,0:15:45.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Move it, you idiot! \NSecond wave cannot take off!{/it's in the way of re-attack/second wave}
Dialogue: 0,0:15:45.98,0:15:51.18,Default,,0,0,0,,Jettison into the sea anything that clutters the deck!{lit is "scraps/damages" the deck but I think he meant this} \NNo worry, the sea is warm around here!{/in this area}
Dialogue: 0,0:15:59.50,0:16:01.54,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay, emergency landing!{/landing on water - don't know what it is so trusting HA}
Dialogue: 0,0:16:18.87,0:16:20.08,Default,,0,0,0,,Attaway.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:22.00,0:16:25.19,Default,,0,0,0,,You returned safely! \NHad us all worried here!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:28.40,0:16:30.68,Default,,0,0,0,,Reporting! Our attacking forces...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:30.68,0:16:32.74,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, the results. What are results?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:32.74,0:16:37.66,Default,,0,0,0,,Yessir! According to my observations, \N4 battleships are sunk, 4 more badly damaged.{https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Attack_on_Pearl_Harbor}
Dialogue: 0,0:16:38.28,0:16:39.33,Default,,0,0,0,,So all of them?{zenmetsu is "annihilation; total destruction; complete destruction; crushing defeat"}
Dialogue: 0,0:16:40.01,0:16:42.62,Default,,0,0,0,,Aside from the absent Enterprise and Lexington.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:43.62,0:16:44.87,Default,,0,0,0,,All except carriers?{/all but ...}
Dialogue: 0,0:16:50.30,0:16:51.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Aircraft carriers are intact?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:07.09,0:17:09.87,Default,,0,0,0,,We may strike back, \Nif we hold position for 2 or 3 more days!{unsure if this is the meaning but todomatte is " to remain; to abide; to stay (in the one place)​"}
Dialogue: 0,0:17:09.87,0:17:13.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Don't say nonsense! \NWe don't have any tankers in the vicinity.{/our tanker would have to come from afar}
Dialogue: 0,0:17:13.44,0:17:16.66,Default,,0,0,0,,Can they come at short notice,\Nafter we summon them with Morse?{unsure, maybe he means "do you think if we call it with wireless connection, they'll allocate it for us here?"}
Dialogue: 0,0:17:16.66,0:17:18.37,Default,,0,0,0,,Their carriers are out of shape!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:18.37,0:17:22.68,Default,,0,0,0,,If we hit their air carriers \Neven betraying our location becomes a least worry!{very unsure, lit: even if we hit at least carrier, and end up revealing address to here to the enemy, we don't have a single thing to fear}
Dialogue: 0,0:17:22.68,0:17:23.69,Default,,0,0,0,,So the carriers?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:23.69,0:17:27.90,Default,,0,0,0,,Admiral! Each carrier is ready \Nto maneuver for a 2nd attack!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:27.90,0:17:30.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Do we launch this 2nd wave?{/is there need for reattack}
Dialogue: 0,0:17:32.63,0:17:34.59,Default,,0,0,0,,The foe will definitely strike{/come} again.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:34.59,0:17:36.51,Default,,0,0,0,,Counter measures are in place.{unsure if this is what he means, lit is "what's left of counter-attack mechanisms are ready"}
Dialogue: 0,0:17:36.51,0:17:38.11,Default,,0,0,0,,Any civilian unrest?{/Are the citizens upset?}
Dialogue: 0,0:17:38.11,0:17:41.35,Default,,0,0,0,,People are in disarray.{/Extremely confused} \NThe foe killed the radio broadcast.{I think he means radio facilities have been damaged and not that they willingly stopped it}
Dialogue: 0,0:17:42.27,0:17:43.52,Default,,0,0,0,,How about their carriers?{/then, where are ...}
Dialogue: 0,0:17:44.64,0:17:47.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Allegedly stationed upper south of Wake Island.{/we have concluded they are in the upper southern parts from here - unsure if it's wake island or up there, wake is actually a dedass long way away from and also their carriers headed this way so this would be an extremely stupid thing to surmise, but well}
Dialogue: 0,0:18:07.12,0:18:08.83,Default,,0,0,0,,Dispatch the patrol again.{/release/let out}
Dialogue: 0,0:18:09.42,0:18:11.29,Default,,0,0,0,,Admiral, let's sweep the north.{/over northern ocean area}
Dialogue: 0,0:18:11.94,0:18:17.11,Default,,0,0,0,,Coming from the south would make a lot more sense.{/the common sense is ...} \NListen, we have to find the Japanese carriers...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:17.80,0:18:19.22,Default,,0,0,0,,And then, obliterate them.{/smash/crish}
Dialogue: 0,0:18:21.93,0:18:23.87,Default,,0,0,0,,How about operation's objectives?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:23.87,0:18:24.71,Default,,0,0,0,,All are met.{/accomplished}
Dialogue: 0,0:18:25.21,0:18:30.71,Default,,0,0,0,,The American Pacific Fleet won't be able \Nto operate from Pearl Harbor within the next 6 months.{/won't be able to dispatch/sortie out from ... within next ...}
Dialogue: 0,0:18:30.71,0:18:34.41,Default,,0,0,0,,We favorably protected the flanks and the rear \Nof Southern operation.{/fleets/gaining a free hand in southern waters}
Dialogue: 0,0:18:34.41,0:18:37.18,Default,,0,0,0,,We have orders to launch multiple attacks!{/in our orders, the attack should be repeated/reiterated/cycled}
Dialogue: 0,0:18:40.26,0:18:44.68,Default,,0,0,0,,We are also ordered to be as wary as possible, \Nmaking sure casualties are minimal.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:44.68,0:18:46.50,Default,,0,0,0,,How is the enemy's condition?{/how is enemy looking}
Dialogue: 0,0:18:46.98,0:18:50.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Reports say, they've significantly bolstered their counterattack response.{lit: It is estimated that a considerable counterattack ability has been restored.}
Dialogue: 0,0:18:50.92,0:18:54.75,Default,,0,0,0,,2nd wave attack losses are of 24 planes for us.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:54.75,0:18:56.92,Default,,0,0,0,,A next wave would come with more losses.{lit is "reattack preparations are not completed" but HA has it "If you re-attack, you have to take the risk."}
Dialogue: 0,0:18:57.32,0:18:59.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Besides, the enemy aircraft carrier...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:00.04,0:19:01.62,Default,,0,0,0,,Let's go for the night attack!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:01.62,0:19:05.43,Default,,0,0,0,,For this purpose, we have a special \Nnight-time torpedo bombing team!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:06.22,0:19:08.02,Default,,0,0,0,,Are you suggesting a gamble?{having to believe HA here as I don't know what he is saying, bakushi is "death from explosion; death from bombing" and I dunno what it means, maybe "so you suggest we wait here like sitting ducks?"}
Dialogue: 0,0:19:08.52,0:19:10.65,Default,,0,0,0,,A better gambit \Nthan just returning!{/Better than returning without playing the trump!}
Dialogue: 0,0:19:10.65,0:19:12.05,Default,,0,0,0,,Aviation officers!{/Aviation staff.}
Dialogue: 0,0:19:12.53,0:19:15.53,Default,,0,0,0,,It's risky to get too involved \Ninto strategy planning.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:15.53,0:19:19.99,Default,,0,0,0,,We aim to sensibly balance attacks efficiency\Nwith our limited force.{lit: Consider the balance between the spirit of attack and the limited force.}
Dialogue: 0,0:19:19.99,0:19:23.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Japan's industrial capabilities \Ncannot vouch for repeated mistakes.{/don't allow us to build battleships casually/are not meant for mass-producing warships}
Dialogue: 0,0:19:23.81,0:19:28.25,Default,,0,0,0,,But the grand-admiral of the Navy wants us \Nto kill as many birds with one stone as we can.{to sink as many enemy ships as possible in one go/with one stone}{something like the highest possible navy promotion, commander in chief of the total armada}
Dialogue: 0,0:19:30.39,0:19:32.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Westward, the weather is against us.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:32.44,0:19:36.13,Default,,0,0,0,,While taking off is possible, \Nlanding is something else entirely.{lit: for landing, the situation on our side is bad}
Dialogue: 0,0:19:43.59,0:19:45.01,Default,,0,0,0,,What can this mean?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:45.85,0:19:49.48,Default,,0,0,0,,As you can see, we've taken the course \Nto the north-northwest.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:49.48,0:19:51.06,Default,,0,0,0,,There won't be any more waves?{/reattack is cancelled}
Dialogue: 0,0:19:51.06,0:19:54.09,Default,,0,0,0,,I told them not to call it off. \NDamn it, this is frustrating.{unsure what he means lit is "I didn't say cancelled" but I think he means what I wrote}
Dialogue: 0,0:19:54.09,0:19:56.27,Default,,0,0,0,,They say admirals are prone to panic attacks.{unsure what he means, lit: a lot of nervous breakdowns in choukan alone}
Dialogue: 0,0:19:56.27,0:19:59.18,Default,,0,0,0,,They see airplanes \Nas a mere axillary {attacking }force.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:59.18,0:20:03.53,Default,,0,0,0,,All they value are the big gunned ships,{/they only value/prioritize the battleships} \Nmisunderstanding this new era of warfare.{/they don't understand the times are about to take a big turn}
Dialogue: 0,0:20:04.07,0:20:06.12,Default,,0,0,0,,Always so timorous, damn it.{guess, HA has it "that's right" which is obviously not right, I hear doudai sugira iyada - "what about it, too much disgusting" - no clue what it means, maybe "this is too abhorring to me"?}
Dialogue: 0,0:20:06.12,0:20:07.74,Default,,0,0,0,,Seniority fries their brain.{lit: seniority by length of service to go straight to one's head (of alcohol); to feel the effects (of an illness); to lose one's wits} {/Length of service had gone to their heads}
Dialogue: 0,0:20:07.74,0:20:09.29,Default,,0,0,0,,If only it was up to Yamaguchi...{unsure what he means, most likely yamaguchi is this lower-rank officer we're seeing right now, can't find any in wikipedia}
Dialogue: 0,0:20:10.83,0:20:13.79,Default,,0,0,0,,Prepare an airplane{actually dase is let out/dispatch}! \NI'm going to the Headquarters on Akagi.{kikan is "agency; organisation; organization; institution; organ; body" so I think here he means the General Headquarters located on Akagi}
Dialogue: 0,0:20:13.79,0:20:14.65,Default,,0,0,0,,Captain!{abs. guess}
Dialogue: 0,0:20:14.65,0:20:17.04,Default,,0,0,0,,Forget it, I'll do it myself!{guess, but kasero may be "let me go"} \NI'll talk to the Chief!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:18.17,0:20:20.05,Default,,0,0,0,,Let me go! \NThis is a mutiny! Let me go!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:21.34,0:20:24.89,Default,,0,0,0,,The Japanese army's landing at Barbers Point \Nproved to be false{dema is false rumor (rumour); groundless rumor; misinformation​}.{https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Naval_Air_Station_Barbers_Point}
Dialogue: 0,0:20:24.89,0:20:29.47,Default,,0,0,0,,All we hear is falses.{lit: I'm already tired of hearing dema} \NThe actual Japanese army isn't as much of a bogeyman.{lit: what's scary now is without japanese army the dema} {/We're not as scared of actual Japanese army as of rumors}
Dialogue: 0,0:20:29.47,0:20:32.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Infantry reports \Ncountless cases of friendly fire.{lit: soldiers shoot how many times at anything that moves}
Dialogue: 0,0:20:32.06,0:20:35.05,Default,,0,0,0,,Out of 17 liaison aircraft from Enterprise, \N7 were shot down as this.{the Enterprise sent out 17 planes, only 7 of which were downed by friendly anti-air, when you get to the moment they say "all 7 planes were reported shot down" consider removing "all" if you'd like}
Dialogue: 0,0:20:35.05,0:20:38.07,Default,,0,0,0,,Excuse me, radar station reports, \Nthe enemy is to the north.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:38.07,0:20:40.92,Default,,0,0,0,,However, why is there no new wave of attack?{/reattacks stopped coming}
Dialogue: 0,0:20:40.92,0:20:43.07,Default,,0,0,0,,Our gasoline tank is still untouched.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:46.12,0:20:50.23,Default,,0,0,0,,Now that they've done it, \Nwe're probably due to retreat to San Francisco.{tettai is evacuation; withdrawal; revocation; repeal; retreat}
Dialogue: 0,0:20:50.23,0:20:52.91,Default,,0,0,0,,Pearl Harbor waters are shallow. \NThe vessels will be easily fished up.{lit: ships quickly get pulled}
Dialogue: 0,0:20:52.91,0:20:55.67,Default,,0,0,0,,This once again \Nproved battleships obsolescence.{lit: by getting sunk, such a wretched ship did seisei - no clue what's this about, maybe "precedent"? because I don't see how the battleships can be deemed guilty for getting sunk in this situation; HA has it "I'm glad that such a rag ship sunk"}
Dialogue: 0,0:20:55.67,0:21:00.59,Default,,0,0,0,,Hardline lawmakers, whether they like it or not, \Nwill finally see aircraft carriers as the future.{/With this, even the hard-headed lawmakers will admit that the era of naval aircraft has arrived, even if they don't like it.}
Dialogue: 0,0:21:00.59,0:21:02.09,Default,,0,0,0,,The old man will be thrilled.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:02.09,0:21:02.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Old man?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:03.26,0:21:05.05,Default,,0,0,0,,President Roosevelt.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:05.05,0:21:08.45,Default,,0,0,0,,As a proponent of carriers theory, \Nhe wants them mass produced.{/he wants to build many ..., impatient to do it}
Dialogue: 0,0:21:08.45,0:21:11.08,Default,,0,0,0,,They went for this strategy, \Nwithout rounding it off...{lit: when fighting with an operation like this, they don't pursue it/make doubly sure - I think he means that they didn't go for more waves of attack}{/they don't bring it to completion}
Dialogue: 0,0:21:11.08,0:21:12.93,Default,,0,0,0,,Did their commanders wussy out?{/Could it be because their commanders were too craven for this?}
Dialogue: 0,0:21:12.93,0:21:14.23,Default,,0,0,0,,Or was it...{/unless}
Dialogue: 0,0:21:15.04,0:21:16.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Or was it?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:17.60,0:21:18.63,Default,,0,0,0,,A trap?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:20.76,0:21:24.09,Default,,0,0,0,,Our submarine located an enemy fleet \Nheading for Pearl Harbor.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:26.36,0:21:27.69,Default,,0,0,0,,Enterprise, too?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:29.41,0:21:31.73,Default,,0,0,0,,Must be. The likelihood of that is very high.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:31.73,0:21:32.85,Default,,0,0,0,,Just a likelihood?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:32.85,0:21:35.37,Default,,0,0,0,,Isn't our survival hanging on likelihoods!?{lit: didn't we came here betting on chances}
Dialogue: 0,0:21:36.17,0:21:38.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Idiot! One strikes the iron while it's still hot!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:39.54,0:21:42.34,Default,,0,0,0,,There is a time to scatter stones \Nand a time to gather them.{HA has it " It is difficult to store the sword in the scabbard." and I think he is right, this is supposed to mean something like "it may be hard, but there are times when you just have to sheathe your sword patiently" or "you don't throw fists after the fight is over"}
Dialogue: 0,0:21:57.10,0:21:58.02,Default,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:59.46,0:22:04.03,Default,,0,0,0,,Admiral, I have a suggestion.{advice (to a superior); counsel; proposal; suggestion; recommendation} \NOperation's objectives were met.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:04.03,0:22:05.90,Default,,0,0,0,,We now lack Intel on the enemy.{/enemy condition is unknown}
Dialogue: 0,0:22:05.90,0:22:09.53,Default,,0,0,0,,And due to the bad weather coming our way, \Nour fuel supply is at risk.{HA: Due to bad weather on allies, refueling is also being struck.}
Dialogue: 0,0:22:10.20,0:22:13.98,Default,,0,0,0,,I think, we better return the whole fleet \Nback to Japan safely, while we can.{HA: I think we should safely return the fleet to Japan now.}
Dialogue: 0,0:22:14.73,0:22:18.52,Default,,0,0,0,,The true battlefield for our Imperial Navy \Nlies in the southern waters.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:19.00,0:22:23.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Shouldn't we crush the enemy \Nin a determinant battle of fleets, fair and square?{HA: Let's show its true value in the fleet decisive battle. - I want to also add "evidential/demonstrative" but I can't find the right word or place}
Dialogue: 0,0:22:23.92,0:22:26.95,Default,,0,0,0,,That's right, the Indian Ocean awaits!{ryo is not ocean but I trust HA here}
Dialogue: 0,0:22:29.30,0:22:29.99,Default,,0,0,0,,Course{added} to north!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:37.77,0:22:41.05,Default,,0,0,0,,At that moment, there was no one \Nin Akagi high command,
Dialogue: 0,0:22:41.05,0:22:46.64,Default,,0,0,0,,able to predict, with full confidence, \Nwhat would be the effect of further waves of attack.{Lit: that time, hikan (no clue what is it but may be "pessimistic" or "lower government official"), in the akagi surrounding/environment, more reattacks effect, truly sure of it there was nobody}
Dialogue: 0,0:22:48.80,0:22:52.83,Default,,0,0,0,,And so, it remains arguable to this day, \Nwhether or not extra waves of attack
Dialogue: 0,0:22:52.83,0:22:55.33,Default,,0,0,0,,would have changed the outcome of Pacific War.{/whether or not a re-attack should have been made remains an eternal controversy.}
Dialogue: 0,0:22:57.00,0:23:02.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Some accuse them of cowardice{/criticize for being timid/craven},\Nothers observe a more cautionary attitude.{/careful and respectful}
Dialogue: 0,0:23:03.74,0:23:09.51,Default,,0,0,0,,However, it is said that a truly talented commander \Nwould never lose sight of his objectives,
Dialogue: 0,0:23:09.51,0:23:13.42,Default,,0,0,0,,aptly taking a critical decision \Nwithout batting an eyelash.{/would come up with a right decision in an instant}
Dialogue: 0,0:23:14.68,0:23:19.67,Default,,0,0,0,,Conversely, if you let the situation at hand \Ninfluence your decision at a moment like this, {/on the contrary, if you let emotions take over yourself, losing sight of your objectives,}
Dialogue: 0,0:23:20.27,0:23:24.42,Default,,0,0,0,,no satisfactory result comes out \Nof your objective's oversight.{/the results can only be expected to be insufficient/inadequate}
Dialogue: 0,0:23:26.89,0:23:36.89,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fade(100,0)}The Pacific War taught us the preciousness of peace.\NBut also instilled numerous lessons on how to live.{太平洋戦争はわれわれに平和の尊さを教えたがまた生きるための教訓を数多くのこしている}
Dialogue: 0,0:23:39.29,0:23:41.96,Default,,0,0,0,,June 1942.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:41.96,0:23:44.79,Default,,0,0,0,,Two major task forces - \NJapanese and American
Dialogue: 0,0:23:44.79,0:23:49.07,Default,,0,0,0,,spot one another at a measly distance of just 240km, \Nin the Battle of Midway.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:50.03,0:23:53.24,Default,,0,0,0,,How do you approach the foe, \Nhow do you assess his condition?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:53.24,0:23:54.64,Default,,0,0,0,,And how do you fight him?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:55.30,0:23:58.54,Default,,0,0,0,,The commanders put \Nall of their reckoning and intuition at use.{/The commander puts all of his effort into calculation and judgment.}
Dialogue: 0,0:23:59.75,0:24:02.27,Default,,0,0,0,,Deeming situation favorable,\NAmerica stepped in.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:02.80,0:24:07.61,Default,,0,0,0,,Just as it was about to dispatch its 2nd wave wings, \NJapan's mobile fleet
Dialogue: 0,0:24:07.61,0:24:11.30,Default,,0,0,0,,had been engulfed \Nin a swarm of American dive bombers.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:12.97,0:24:17.16,Default,,0,0,0,,Time is capital! \NHad American bomber attack come 5 minutes too late,
Dialogue: 0,0:24:17.62,0:24:20.10,Default,,0,0,0,,the Battle of Midway \Nwould become a can of worms.{very unsure what's this about, アメリカ爆撃機の来襲が遅ければとミッドウェイ海戦に恨みは残る but I don't care since jikai}
Dialogue: 0,0:24:20.91,0:24:25.15,Default,,0,0,0,,However, was this 5 minutes frame \Nanother stroke of fate?{/coincidence}
Dialogue: 0,0:24:26.49,0:24:31.38,Default,,0,0,0,,The Pacific War is told to have its own Battle of Sekigahara{https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Battle_of_Sekigahara}, \Nwhich is this one, Battle for Midway.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:31.38,0:24:35.33,Default,,0,0,0,,Please witness more fateful decisions \Nbeing taken next week.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:32.89,0:24:39.10,Sign,,0,0,0,,{\fade(0,300)\c&HF4F4F9&\1a&H18&}{ミッドウェイ海戦(前編)}{Animentary: Decision}Episode 2 \NBattle of Midway (Part 1){\N Please look forward to it next week}
Comment: 0,0:24:44.42,0:24:44.46,Default,,0,0,0,,{ch}
Dialogue: 0,0:24:44.46,0:24:48.87,Default,,0,0,30,,If you're a man, let's put your strength to test{男だったら　力を試せ}
Dialogue: 0,0:24:48.87,0:24:53.21,Default,,0,0,30,,If you are a man, keep your hopes sizzling{男だったら　希望(のぞみ)を燃やせ}
Dialogue: 0,0:24:53.21,0:24:57.57,Default,,0,0,30,,If you are a man, don't lose your heart{男だったら　くじけるな}
Dialogue: 0,0:24:57.57,0:25:06.14,Default,,0,0,30,,Because there's just you and me, a man and a man{俺もおまえも　男と男}
Dialogue: 0,0:25:06.14,0:25:14.37,Default,,0,0,30,,With crimson blood flowing in our veins all the same{おなじ真赤な　血が通う}
